The '''IEEE International Symposium on Computer Arithmetic (ARITH)''' is a conference in the area of computer arithmetic.<ref>[http://www.arithsymposium.org/ ARITH Symposium Website]</ref> The symposium was established in 1969, initially as three-year event, then as a biennial event, and, finally, from 2015 as an annual symposium.
ARITH topics span from theoretical aspects and [[algorithm]]s for operations, to hardware implementations of arithmetic units and applications of computer arithmetic.
ARITH symposia are sponsored by [[IEEE Computer Society]].
