{{about|the aquarium in Stralsund, Germany|the aquarium in Rotterdam, Netherlands|Oceanium}} {{Infobox zoo |zoo_name =Ozeaneum |logo = |logo_caption = |image = Ozeaneum in Stralsund, Eingang.JPG |image_caption = Ozeaneum Stralsund |location = [[Stralsund]], [[Germany]] |date_opened = July 2008 |date_closed = |coordinates = {{coord|54|18|56|N|13|5|49|E|type:landmark_region:DE-MV_source:dewiki|display=inline,title}} |area = |num_species = |num_animals = |largest_tank_vol = {{convert|2600000|l|USgal|abbr=on}} |total_tank_vol = |annual_visitors = 1 million (first 12 months)<ref name="zoo_award"/> |members = |exhibits = |website = {{URL|http://www.Ozeaneum.com}} }}
'''Ozeaneum''' is a [[public aquarium]] in the [[Germany|German]] city of [[Stralsund]]. It is a main attraction of the [[German Oceanographic Museum]] (''Deutsches Meeresmuseum''), arguably one of the three largest institutions of its kind in Europe.
The Ozeaneum — located at the historical Stralsund harbour on the [[Baltic Sea|Baltic]] coast — opened its doors in July 2008. It displays primarily [[sea life]] of the [[North Sea]] and the Baltic Sea.
The Ozeaneum was expected to be a major tourist attraction, and receive 550,000 visitors per year. It proved to be considerably more attractive than expected, and by the end of the first year had already had over 900,000 visitors. The millionth visit occurred on 27 July 2009.
On 22 May 2010, the OZEANEUM Stralsund received the [[European Museum of the Year Award]] in a ceremony in the [[Finland|Finnish]] town of [[Tampere]].<ref name="zoo_award"/>
